>just reimport and replace the whole mesh
yes. the workflow is a bit of a pain in the ass but it's nothing too complicated. in blunder, make sure each animation is pushed as its own NLA track, and animation optimization is turned OFF at export or you'll get pic related. i find that .glb/gltf works the best, as it supports animations out-of-the-box. all the models in skate club are rigify'd characters exported as glb, then resaved in-engine as their own scene.
